what is hindering open source adoption in the education space, and what systems are in place to prevent it from moving forward.

Open Source Software(OSS) is a software development philosophy based on public accessibility of a software source code.  The aim is to enable interested parties to audit the software, enhance it or modify it for any specific use case.  Having the freedom to modify and learn from those that came before seems like a perfect match for an educational environment, so why hasn't an open philosophy permeated further into the educational sphere.  Most educational institutions in North America fall into two major software camps; Google Suite, or Microsoft 365.  This monopolization of the educational ecosystem serves to enhance the standing of 
